President Barack Obama addressed the nation to announce the end of combat operations in Iraq. He emphasized that this milestone should inspire confidence and commitment in shaping America's future and reaffirm the country's intention to sustain and strengthen its leadership in the world. The President expressed his pride in the courage and sacrifice of America's men and women in uniform, as well as their families. He highlighted the fulfillment of his pledge to bring combat brigades out of Iraq and transfer responsibility for security to the Iraqi people. The President stated that ending the war in Iraq is not only in Iraq's interest but also in America's interest, as the United States has made significant sacrifices to empower the Iraqi people. He emphasized the need to focus on restoring the economy, creating jobs, strengthening the middle class, improving education, and reducing dependence on foreign oil.